{
  "text": "the average steady-state reduction of I Ba peak amplitude for concentrations of -AgaTxIVA \u0546100 nM was 74 \u03ee 4% (n \u03ed 21 neurons). The effect of -AgaTxIVA was not reversed after a \u05465-min washing (data not shown) and was not reversed by depolarizing prepulses (Fig. 5B) in contrast with the observation of [CITATION_1] in rat neurons. The persistence of a residual current in high concentrations of -AgaTxIVA (\u0546100 nM) suggests the presence in these neurons of an -AgaTxIVA-resistant current component.",
